Program: Last Word
Title: Brian Haw, Mike Waterson, Yelena Bonner and Mietek Pemper
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b012078k
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 26 Jun 2011
Matthew Bannister on Brian Haw - the anti war protester who camped in Parliament Square for ten years; Mike Waterson who made singing traditional British music a family affair; Yelena Bonner - wife of the Soviet dissident Andrei Sakharov - and campaigner in her own right Mietek Pemper - the Jewish secretary who helped to type Schindler's List and saved thousands from the gas chamber And Gunnar Fischer - the cinematographer who gave the films of Ingmar Bergman their distinctive look. Show less